<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="bAuWhpDPmVGgDaepoowJukwlfVQsJPdR">Comparisons</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p>Java also allows me to compare different variables: either against literal
values, or against other variables.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This is basis for <em>simple decision making</em>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="EuddnTejTlEZaIAttmJUDwqxLAWdYNQd">Simple Comparisons</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>// Let's try out ==, !=, &lt;, &lt;=, &gt;, and &gt;=
int tester = 10;
// This is equality
System.out.println(tester == 10);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="kfjlldprRQUOtUaTuYveJPZEbFCgHlCU">A Common Mistake</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="ulist lead">
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>a = 10</code> means <strong>set a to 10</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>a == 10</code> means <strong>test if a is equal to 10</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="uOanIxfYhyBAYDDSDumbwovkhBiwNNcg">Don&#8217;t Get Confused</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>int tester = 10;
// This is equality
System.out.println(tester == 10);
// This is not
System.out.println(tester = 5);
System.out.println(tester);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="NZRZqEBsBPejsjEIMEUExRtpUZwnPHvN">Comparisons Against Variables</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>// Let's try out ==, !=, &lt;, &lt;=, &gt;, and &gt;=
int first = 10;
int second = 20;
System.out.println(first &gt; first);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="JXtQIUEitmTgnNBVMLHYYnkyMeHylXzT">More Complex Comparisons</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>// Let's try out ==, !=, &lt;, &lt;=, &gt;, and &gt;=
int first = 10;
int second = 20;
System.out.println(first + second == 30);
System.out.println(first - second &lt;= 10);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1 oneword">
<h2 id="GieGtJaHsXZBBBMvZqGAdPacxybqOQxP">Questions About Simple Comparisons?</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">

</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="BueiLwuNKbnJPZVcrKBddwHYcdYQyvjx">Compound Comparisons</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p>We can combine multiple comparisons together using logical and (<code>&amp;&amp;</code>) and or
(<code>||</code>) operators.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="vDROZOQyBuCsHvUlGCATsKriCrZxCmeK">! Combining Comparisons</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>int first = 10;
System.out.println(first &gt; 5 &amp;&amp; first &lt; 10);
System.out.println(first &lt; 10 &amp;&amp; first &gt; 5);
System.out.println(first &gt; 10 || first &gt; 5);
System.out.println(first &gt; 10 || false);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="FBXXgCFgySnrwZHYfSoUHPKWaxwklwjZ">Evaluation Order</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p>Conditionals are always evaluated from left to right, and evaluation stops as
soon as the result is known.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="kTKjdTjMotZBlcgraocBlOSIGadWncvF">Comparisons Enable Decisions</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>// Comparisons enable decisions
int first = 10;
if (first &gt; 20) {
  System.out.println("First is greater than 20");
} else {
  System.out.println("First is not greater than 20");
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="ZVszIucHlwfpNThvCPzvAuGXDQoXGDJm"><code>if-else</code></h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p><code>if-else</code> statements are the building block for programmatic decision making:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist s">
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>if</em> something is true, do one thing;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><em>otherwise</em>, if something else is true, do some other thing;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><em>otherwise</em>, if something else is true, do some other thing;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>etc.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="mKZSZKIqiozOhiBMXfrUaxnAYmcEWiNU"><code>if-elseif-elseif-else</code></h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p><code>if</code> statements can have multiple clauses:</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlight"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java">if (firstThing) {
  // do one thing
} else if (secondThing) {
  // do another thing
} else if (thirdThing) {
  // another thing
} else {
  // run if firstThing, secondThing, and thirdThing are all false
}</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><code>else</code> statements are run if no if statement matches.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="CDpGeuKlxKgJwOfLsqWUIfCazJSauLSt">! Only One Statement Runs</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>// Only the first matching branch of if is executed
int comparison = 10;
if (comparison &gt; 5) {
  System.out.println("I'll be executed");
} else if (comparison &gt; 3) {
  System.out.println("I won't be executed");
} else {
  System.out.println("I definitely won't be executed");
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="ulsvDseRWSMaJGiZXigRkKHBdYgQEGwm">Remember: Only One Statement Runs</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p><strong>In any if statement, only one statement is executed.</strong>*</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="sCTwbrbupLHdZwRvBbUQlfGFoutbJTfB">Somewhat Useful Example</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>// Create an int called numSuperBowls, and then add 1 to it
// if patriotsWinAgain is true</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="fcnIiRcbbDBZyWPgBSCPEDBMiSUCxLEy">Nested Conditionals</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p><code>if</code> statements can be nested inside other <code>if</code> statements</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlight"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java">if (testMe) {
  if (testMeAgain) {
    // I am well tested
  } else {
    // I'm only moderated well-tested
  }
} else {
  // You need to write better tests
}</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="ySgvSxVBLXrmJCUTffzlhLYXqdWCKBeX">!Practice With Nested Conditionals</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>// What should we decide today?</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="PgMLuXcxwdrkzLNqnpFFWLNAsIHpiYTB">Variable Scope</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p><code>if</code> statements provide our first example of a <em>block</em> of code.</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlight"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java">if (...) {
  // I'm a block of code
}</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="ulist s">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Blocks are enclosed by braces and can have multiple statements</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Variables declared <em>inside</em> a block are not visible <em>outside</em> it&#8230;&#8203;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>But variables declared outside (and prior to) a block <em>are</em> visible <em>inside</em> it</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="ECKCAOoavGvvNXrOtQqqIZMxNKnbmBAj">!Practice With Scope</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>int outside = 5;
if (true) {
  int inside = 10;
  System.out.println(outside);
}
System.out.println(inside);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="uyjfRCHsbnKWGDOzAwWeAPodEDLQbWjP">Indentation Hints</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph lead">
<p>Assuming you are indenting your code properly, a general rule of thumb about
scope:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist s">
<ul>
<li>
<p>You <strong>can</strong> access variables "to the left"</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>You <strong>cannot</strong> access variables "to the right"</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>(Where directions are defined relative to the start of the line of code you are
writing.)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="eUWkVtCUwaoLWfYANZKlTLvlRthqeEIz">!Practice With Scope</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="literalblock janini">
<div class="content">
<pre>int outside = 5;
if (true) {
  int inside = 10;
  // outside is to my left, so OK
  System.out.println(outside);
}
// inside is to my right, so bad
System.out.println(inside);</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
